HOUSE JOINT RESOLUTION 937
By Atchley
A RESOLUTION to honor and recognize Chief John Linsenbigler,
longtime officer with the Seymour Volunteer Fire
Department, on the occasion of his retirement.
WHEREAS, it is fitting that the members of this General Assembly should specially
recognize those Tennesseans who have performed with uncommon devotion and ability
throughout their careers in public service; and
WHEREAS, one such outstanding person is John Linsenbigler, who is taking a well-
earned retirement on April 1, 2026, after a distinguished forty-four-year career in the fire service;
and
WHEREAS, for thirty years, he has been a vitally important officer with the Seymour
Volunteer Fire Department (SVFD) and has astutely served as its chief and executive officer for
the past seven years; and
WHEREAS, after moving to Seymour in 1980, John Linsenbigler started his fire career
as a reserve firefighter for Rural Metro Fire in 1982 and then began working on Rural Metro
ambulances in 1985; and
WHEREAS, in 1989, he transferred to Johnson Bible College's Fire Brigade, and he
began a seventeen-year tenure as the college's fire chief in 1995; and
WHEREAS, because of an ongoing partnership with the college, SVFD hired Mr.
Linsenbigler to oversee a grant in 1996, and a long and mutually beneficial relationship was
established; and
WHEREAS, John Linsenbigler proceeded to climb the SVFD leadership ladder, earning
promotion to lieutenant in 1999, captain in 2004, assistant chief in 2008, deputy chief in 2010,
and in 2017 he became the chief; and
HJR0937
013177
- 1 -

WHEREAS, John Linsenbigler has always been a servant-leader, focusing on the
welfare of his fellow human beings and community care, and he has utilized a hands-on
approach to his leadership of SVFD, including delivering a baby and providing comfort to a burn
victim; and
WHEREAS, at the time of his retirement, SVFD will be celebrating its fifty-fifth
anniversary as a community fire agency; the proud legacy he is leaving behind includes six
stations and seventy-eight firefighters (with seven applicants pending) who serve some 16,000
households, responding to 3,229 emergency calls in 2025 alone; and
WHEREAS, Mr. Linsenbigler plans to continue his community service as a substitute
teacher with the Sevier County school system; and
WHEREAS, he and his family express their faith as members of Seymour Heights
Christian Church; and
WHEREAS, his many personal and professional accomplishments aside, John
Linsenbigler is most grateful for the love and companionship he shares with his wife of forty-five
years, Carol, a teacher with more than twenty years of experience; and
WHEREAS, the Linsenbiglers have been blessed with two children, Rebecca and Adam,
and two granddaughters; and
WHEREAS, John Linsenbigler has been a visionary and compassionate leader during
his tenure with the Seymour Volunteer Fire Department, and he should be specially recognized
on this special occasion; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES OF THE ONE HUNDRED
FOURTEENTH GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE SENATE
CONCURRING, that we honor and commend Chief John Linsenbigler upon his exemplary thirty
years of service to the Seymour Volunteer Fire Department, salute his ongoing commitment to
- 2 - 013177

his community and its safety, and extend to him our best wishes for a happy and fulfilling
retirement.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that an appropriate copy of this resolution be prepared
for presentation with this final clause omitted from such copy and upon proper request made to
the appropriate clerk, the language appearing immediately following the State seal appear
without House or Senate designation.
